# Static security headers (Netlify / Cloudflare Pages "_headers" convention).
#
# IMPORTANT — static-host reality:
#   GitHub Pages (the current host) does NOT honor this file and cannot set
#   custom HTTP response headers. On GitHub Pages the ACTIVE security-header
#   layer is the <meta http-equiv> set already baked into templates/base.html
#   (Content-Security-Policy, X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options,
#   referrer). This file is therefore:
#     * inert on GitHub Pages (served as a harmless text asset), and
#     * automatically applied IF the site is ever fronted by an edge that reads
#       "_headers" (Cloudflare Pages, Netlify) — no template/UI change needed.
#
#   These headers change response metadata only — they add ZERO visible UI and
#   cannot break CSS/JS. CSP is intentionally NOT duplicated here to avoid
#   drifting from the proven meta-tag CSP in base.html; manage CSP there.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
